quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  48,16,"Say to the ignorant who stayed behind, “You will soon be called against a nation of great military strength – to fight against them or that they become Muslims; so if you obey, Allah will give you an excellent reward; and if you turn away, the way you had turned away before, He will mete out a painful punishment to you.”"
  48,17,"There is no reproach upon the blind, nor reproach against the lame, nor reproach upon the sick; and whoever obeys Allah and His Noble Messenger – Allah will admit him into Gardens beneath which rivers flow; and whoever turns away – He will mete out a painful punishment to him."
  48,18,"Indeed Allah was truly pleased with the believers when they swore allegiance to you beneath the tree – so He knew what was in their hearts – He therefore sent down peace upon them, and rewarded them with an imminent victory."
  48,19,"And plenty of war booty, to take; and Allah is Most Honourable, Wise."
  48,20,"Allah has promised you plenty of booty which you will take, and has bestowed this to you quickly, and restrained peoples’ hands from you; and in order that it may be a sign for the believers, and to guide you on the Straight Path."
  48,21,"And one more, not within your capacity, is within Allah’s hold; and Allah is Able to do all things."
  48,22,"And if the disbelievers were to fight you, they will turn away and flee, and then they will not find any supporter nor any aide."
  48,23,"The tradition of Allah, ongoing since before; and you will not find the tradition of Allah changing."
